et Command s national Order of Merit List  Within the Corps of Cadets  Chang served as battalion S 2 lieutenant for Echo Company his 1st Class year  In that capacity  he was responsible for ensuring the rats in his battalion kept up their grades and learned sound study habits  After graduation  Chang commissioned in the U S  Army  He was sent to Ft  Benning  Ga  for training  before attending Army Ranger school   Regardless of what I am going for or what I will be in the future  VMI has completely transformed my character  Honor  integrity  and respect   those are the key words that describe what I ve learned at VMI  Hometown  Port Washington  N Y  Major  Computer Science   Share this entry Share on Facebook Share on Twitter Share on Google  Share on Linkedin Share on Tumblr Share on Reddit Share by Mail Stories   Videos Stories   Video Home Stories Slideshows Day in the Life Video Library Admissions Video More About Life at VMI Cadets Academics Athletics Challenge Alumni Faculty and Staff Apply Now Viewbook Links College Fairs FAQs Financial Aid Tuition   Fees Schedule VMI s Institutional Profile Follow  Then lead  Resources VMI CEEB Code  005858 Financial Aid FAFSA Code  003753 Students and their families are encouraged to use a variety of information sources to select a college and major  The State Council of Higher Education for Virginia  SCHEV  provides one such source that is available here  Contact Us VMI Office of Admissions 319 Letcher Avenue Lexington  VA 24450 P  540 464 7211 P  800 767 4207 F  540 464 7746 admissions vmi edu Don t do ordinary  EXPERIENCE VISIT APPLY COSTS   AID CONTACT Seeing Dividends Beyond the Classroom   Scroll to top 